$ DOM example: offsetWidth / offsetHeight

An *element's* `offsetWidth` and `offsetHeight` evalute to the width and height that an element actually occupies. Included in these dimensions is
  • border
  • padding
  • vertical scrollbar (if shown)
Not included is the element's margin.

